The paper deals with low-dimensional embeddings of knowledge graphs and behavior graphs, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) tasks such as predicting unobserved edges and content recommendation. The paper also discusses a Bayesian framework for integrating information from these graphs, which falls under the category of Bayesian methods (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper evaluates its method on datasets related to Freebase and e-commerce, which are commonly used in information retrieval (cs.IR) and database (cs.DB) research.
